Talk Time x Orbseer
CryptoMusicBox #01

Talk Time CryptoMusicBoxes are powered by the blockchain and collected from the finest curio shops in the metaverse.

-----

Song: Dead Weight
Album: Necessary Evil

"my dear, how do we survive the teeth of this modern life?

Musically this song takes some inspiration from one of our all time favorite tunes--Prince's 1999 opener "Let's Get Crazy". The track opens with Prince preaching carpe diem to a rapturous congregation, and to not let the devil ("elevator" was his metaphor for the Devil according to His greatness) take us down. "Dead Weight" is less carpe diem--and more let's learn to deal with the devils within us in order to prevent destruction and extinctions. вЂњLet's Get CrazyвЂќ came out in 1982 and helped open a decade of excess and decadence, while "Dead Weight" is much more introspective, and is going to be released during a pandemic and social and economic unrest, and reflects the constant existential crises we're going through as individuals and as a species right now.

-----

Each CryptoMusicBox comes with the following:

вЂў High Resolution mp4 file that loops to the full song

вЂў Printable 11x17 album art poster file

вЂў Holders of CryptoMusicBox NFTs will receive future airdrops of Talk Time NFTs, AR experiences, and token-gated access to Talk Time live shows/streams.
